ANOTHER KZN cop was shot on Wednesday.The police officer was shot and injured during a gun battle between cops and robbers in Isipingo, south of Durban.During the exchange of gunfire, one suspect died at the scene and an unlicensed firearm was found next to him. The other four suspects managed to escape.The injured cop was part of the K9 unit that responded to a business robbery on Rana Road.Garrith Jamieson, spokesman for Rescue Care Paramedics, said they arrived to find an active shooting scene.&ldquo;Police escorted our medics through dense bush to find the injured officer. &ldquo;He was treated for a gunshot wound and was carried to a police helicopter. &ldquo;The officer was then airlifted to St Augustine&rsquo;s Hospital,&rdquo; he said.KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said charges of business robbery and attempted murder are being investigated by police. Two KwaDabeka cops were also shot and injured in Clermont, west of Durban, on Sunday when they responded to a hijacking.Last month, two other cops were shot and injured when they attended to a complaint of hijacking in Thembeni.